From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Sat, 11 Jul 2026 10:25:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] mmdevapi: Register fresh DualSense mono AudioEndpoint.

Spider-Man Remastered needs the fake SWD/MMDEVAPI AudioEndpoint devnode for
its startup controller-effect binding path. Keeping the Sony controller mono
speaker MMDevice-only lets the game enumerate the endpoint but it never opens
the controller effect stream when the controller is already connected before
launch.

The current path removes stale DualSense / DualSense Edge / DualShock speaker
AudioEndpoint devnodes first. After that cleanup, allow registration of one
fresh AudioEndpoint for the current mono endpoint instead of keeping old
disconnected controller state alive.
---
 dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
index 11111111111..22222222222 100644
--- a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
+++ b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
@@ -1080,6 +1080,7 @@ static void MMDevice_Register(const WCHAR *instguid, const WCHAR *friendly_name,
         if (skip_audioendpoint && is_dualsense_device_path(device_path))
         {
             remove_dualsense_audioendpoint_devices();
+            skip_audioendpoint = FALSE;
         }
 
         if (skip_audioendpoint)
